<P>
   BUDDHA-BIRTHPLACE (Lumbini, Nepal) _ Some 2,500 years ago, on a
spring day under a full moon, Siddhartha Gautama was born in
Lumbini. His mother had gone into labor while on a stroll in a
verdant grove, smelling the flowers and listening to the songbirds.
The baby would grow up to be the Enlightened One _ the Buddha _ and
this village would become holy soil to millions of Buddhists who,
for the most part, would these days never think of coming here. By
Barry Bearak.
</P>
