has resisted court orders to place Reform and Conservative Jews on
the all-Orthodox, taxpayer-financed religious councils that wield
tremendous power in every town and city of this country. Now, with
all appeals exhausted, the Religious Affairs Ministry faces a
Supreme Court deadline to integrate the councils by the end of
December and fierce pressure from Orthodox groups here and in the
United States to defy it. By Deborah Sontag.
