</P>
<P>
   Hicks himself was quick to note that this was not a move born of
post-Johnson anxiety.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not saying he wouldn't have done both Randy and Rafael, if
the opportunity presented itself,'' Hicks said.
</P>
<P>
   The new owner was confident that, yes, there would be Life After
Randy Johnson. Melvin would see to it.
</P>
<P>
   Call it Plan B. There really was one, after all.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
