<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-BILLUPS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS' UNDRAFTED FREE AGENT BILLUPS COMES IN HANDY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Almost lost amid the criticism of the Cowboys'
secondary in the 46-36 Thanksgiving Day loss to the Minnesota
Vikings was the play of rookie cornerback Terry Billups.
</P>
<P>
   Who?
</P>
<P>
   That's the reaction Cowboys fans had when Billups, whom the
Cowboys moved from the practice squad to the active roster last
week, replaced an injured Kevin Smith at left cornerback for much
of the Vikings game.
</P>
<P>
   Sure, Billups earned a spot on Randy Moss' personal highlight
film, along with other toasted members of the Cowboys secondary.
</P>
<P>
   But in the words of Cowboys coach Chan Gailey _ who said the
Cowboys signed Billups for depth purposes, but didn't expect him to
play that much in the game _ he ``acquitted himself well.''
</P>
<P>
   Billups has acquitted himself well despite not starting his
final two seasons at North Carolina. However, Billups, who roomed
with Cowboys top pick Greg Ellis in college, refused to give up the
dream of playing pro football.
</P>
<P>
   After not being selected in the 1998 NFL draft, he signed as a
free agent with the New England Patriots, but was released before
the season.
</P>
<P>
   He then joined the Miami Dolphins' practice squad for two weeks
before they released him, enabling the Cowboys to pick him up on
Oct. 5.
</P>
<P>
   Seven weeks and a horde of defensive back injuries later,
Billups became a member of the active roster on Nov. 24 and made
his professional debut before a nationally televised audience
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't beat that feeling for nothing in the world _
Thanksgiving Day, my first NFL game and I'm playing for the Dallas
Cowboys,'' Billups said. ``I don't think there is a kid in America
who hasn't been a Cowboy fan from when they were little. I couldn't
have asked for a better script. The only thing better would have
been if we could have won the game.''
</P>
<P>
   It appears he'll get a chance to alter the script against the
New Orleans Saints on Sunday, as injuries to starting cornerbacks
Deion Sanders and Kevin Smith will likely put Billups on the field
again. If he doesn't start, he will play in the Cowboys' nickel
defense and is slated to be the team's primary punt returner.
</P>
<P>
   Billups is ready for it all.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a long road,'' Billup said. ``Nobody expected me to
be here. It was a matter of believing in yourself and having a
great family behind me and belief in the Lord that I would get an
opportunity. I'm just going to play my best.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
