BACK TO THE BATES MOTEL : JOSEPH STEFANO AND THE
</P>
<P>
   REMAKING OF 'PSYCHO' When Alfred Hitchcock's ``Psycho'' opened
in 1960, many people were too scared to take a shower for months.
When Gus Van Sant's remake opens Dec. 4, bathtub sales may
skyrocket once more. The two versions have one other thing in
common : the classic script written by Joe Stefano, which Van Sant
has chosen to use virtually intact, an unheard-of choice in a
remake. The 76-year-old Stefano talks about the new film, the old
film, how he and Hitchcock worked together, how he compares the
