<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Action, humor and fun behind updated `Mask'
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Mask of Zorro'' (PG-13)
</P>
<P>
   Old-fashioned in the nicest way, this throwback to the serials
of yore reinvigorates the legend of the righteous bandito. Anthony
Hopkins plays the original, Z-slashing swashbuckler, whose identity
is discovered and family destroyed by the evil Don Rafael (Stuart
Wilson). Flash forward a couple of decades, and Hopkins is grooming
petty thief Alejandro (Antonio Banderas) to wear the mask as the
new Zorro, and avenge himself on the Don. It's all fun, hokey
stuff, propelled with humor, action, great stunts, and the
chemistry between Banderas and Catherine Zeta-Jones, who proves to
be more than just a pretty face. Grade: B +
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
