<P>
   HARTFORD-PATRIOTS (Hartford, Conn.) _ Connecticut's capital is
no Boston. Next to New York, it's a hamlet. It's the milepost in
between, and suddenly, it no longer seems to care. By Thomas
Farragher. (2 takes) GRAPHIC: 12 picas x 11 inches, ``Financial
fitness.''
</P>
<P>
   BEEDIES-FAD (Boston) -- Beedies, a tiny cigarette from India
that looks like marijuana joints and comes in flavors like cherry
and vanilla are loaded with teen-age cachet. But the unfiltered
smokes pack twice the tar and nicotine as a Marlboro -- at half the
cost. By Ellen O'Brien. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ New York State is starving schools to
build prisons. By Derrick Jackson.
</P>
<P>
