<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ If strangers from another planet
were to study the policy stands taken by Democratic and Republican
presidential hopefuls, they might wonder what, if any, the
differences are between the two parties. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
