   &UR; Other Financial &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:45 p.m., the Dow industrial average was
down 133 points. Elsewhere, prices rose 1 percent in Tokyo and 0.8
percent in Hong Kong. They declined 1.4 percent in Frankfurt and
were flat in London. They fell 0.9 percent in Brazil and 0.2
percent in Mexico. On the American debt market, the long bond was
off 9/32 point at midday, with the yield at 5.03 percent. By Robert
D. Hershey.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ Java's creator, James Gosling
of Sun Microsystems, takes the stand today at the Microsoft trial
and is expected to say the software company saw Java as a threat
because of its cross-platform capabilities and became determined to
stop its spread. By Joel Brinkley.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-GATES (New York) _ Microsoft CEO Gates gives a speech
in Manhattan. By Steve Lohr.
