   (Adds: CLINTON-SCANDAL; CLINTON-PAKISTAN; HEADWATERS-FOREST;
SOUL-TRAIN; TEXAS-ESCAPE; WILD-ESCAPE; SHUTTLE-COUNTDOWN;
FBC-A&AMP;M-DEFENSE; and FBC-KSU-DEFENSE.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For Thursday:
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SCANDAL (Washington) _ A federal judge grants permission
to House impeachment investigators to review confidential Justice
Department memos laying out evidence of alleged fund-raising
irregularities in President Clinton's 1996 campaign. By JOHN C.
HENRY and NANCY MATHIS.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-PAKISTAN (Washington) _ President Clinton meets with
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif of Pakistan on a plan to repay the
South Asian nation some of the $658 million it paid for F-16
fighter planes that were never delivered. By NANCY MATHIS.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HEADWATERS-FOREST (Sacramento, Calif.) _ A respected federal
scientist says the environmental plan designed to protect a forest
in Northern California from loggers is inadequate and will cause
more mudslides and the probable elimination of a run of endangered
coho salmon. By ROBERT SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   SOUL-TRAIN (San Francisco) _ A singing driver for the Municipal
Railway has been disciplined for disrupting the peace with his
renditions of soul classics. Cornelius Perdue, 55, was told to turn
off the speakers on his train when a man who lives along the line
complained about the crooning. By RAY DELGADO. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-ESCAPE (Huntsville, Texas) _ Attorneys have been kept away
from the six men who tried to flee from death row with escaped
killer Martin Gurule. Relatives of those men also say they have
been unable to get any information about them. By ALLAN TURNER.
</P>
<P>
   WILD-ESCAPES (Undated) _ Prison administrators around the
country are following the news of Martin Gurule's escape from
Texas' death row with keen interest and, occasionally, real
empathy. While death row escapes are rare, they have happened
before, along with some other notable prison escapes. By KIM COBB.
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE-COUNTDOWN (Undated) _ A dismal weather forecast for
early Thursday threatens to postpone the launch of the shuttle
Endeavour on a mission to haul components of the nascent
international space station into orbit. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-A&AMP;M-DEFENSE (College Station, Texas) _ The defense has saved
the day for Texas A&AMP;M throughout this 10-2 season, but the Wrecking
Crew faces a stiff challenge this week in trying to stop undefeated
Kansas State and quarterback Michael Bishop. By W.H. STICKNEY.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-KSU-DEFENSE (Manhattan, Kansas) _ Ranked among the national
leaders in virtually every statistical category, the Kansas State
defense is primed to put the clamps on Texas A&AMP;M's struggling
offense this week. By TERRY BLOUNT.
</P>
<P>
   For Sunday:
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ If strangers from another planet
were to study the policy stands taken by Democratic and Republican
presidential hopefuls, they might wonder what, if any, the
differences are between the two parties. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
