<HEADLINE>
SECRET SOCIETY OF HAPPY PEOPLE: GRIN AND SHARE IT
</HEADLINE>
 PEOPLE-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LIZ STEVENS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you're happy and you know it ...
</P>
<P>
   ... keep it to yourself, thanks.
</P>
<P>
   Happiness, it sometimes seems, has gone the way of Tab cola and
Milli Vanilli, fading into oblivion. It's hip to be hopeless,
stylish to be stressed and popular to be a pitiable sap spreading
