<HEADLINE>
EXPANSION PLAN FOR FORT WORTH MUSEUM IS BIG-LEAGUE STEP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JANET TYSON 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ I've always respected the Amon Carter
Museum. Its collections are great. Its staff is sophisticated,
utterly professional and devoted to its mission. The goals are
lofty. The programs are first-class.
