including international success, two Grammy awards and a slew of
multiplatinum albums, Tejano supergroup La Mafia has decided to
call it quits. The news comes on the heels of the September release
of the group's seventh album on Sony Discos, Euforia. The first
single, Pido, was a top 20 hit on Billboard's Hot Latin Tracks
chart. By JOEY GUERRA. (Will be filed in the ``e'' category)
</P>
