MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - Volunteers from the Head Start program
in Parker spent $700 at the Walmart in Calexico, Calif., during the
big day-after-Thanksgiving sale. Then, they made the mistake of
crossing the border into Mexicali. Thirteen hours later, they
crossed back into the United States, minus the toys and an
additional $650. Can you say Grinch in Spanish? By E.J. MONTINI
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
DUKE-HILL (Undated) - Fifty years ago, John Wayne, America's hero,
stood atop a rise overlooking the handsome Santa Cruz Valley near
Nogales and envisioned building a huge family compound. But Wayne
got cancer and died, and his partner in the venture, cattle rancher
Ralph Wingfield said, he ``just got too damned old.'' Now the
670-acre ranch, six miles north of Nogales, is for sale, destined
perhaps to become a resort or single-family homes. Scottsdale
Realtor, Lou Perna, who handles such high-end properties, is
representing the Wayne family. By CAROL SOWERS. Story will move in
the ``F'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GINGERBREAD (Undated) - If you have the urge to create a cute
gingerbread house, my advice is to lie down until the feeling goes
away. With PHOTO and GINGERBREAK-SIDE. By KATHLEEN INGLEY. Story
moved in the ``D'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GINGERBREAD-SIDE (Undated) - If you must, despite Kathleen Ingley's
advice, make a gingerbread house, here's a pattern and how to
proceed. Includes recipe and tips. By JUDY WALKER. Story moved in
the ``D'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
THREE PLACES (Undated) - One Charles Ives piece above all sums up
his New England experience, and it is one of his easiest to digest
and, therefore, most popular. It is ``Three Places in New
England,'' and it describes in music three very precise landscapes.
Sometimes called the New England Symphony, it was written by Ives
between 1903 and 1911. It contains three movements that are
unforgettable impressions of the land and people. With THREE
PLACES-SIDE. By RICHARD NILSEN. Story moved in the ``L'' and ``E''
categories.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
THREE PLACES-SIDE (Undated) - Charles Ives, educated at Yale, and
who became a wealthy insurance executive, was a father figure for
U.S. composers. Charles Ives is the father of American music.
Before him, what American composers wrote for the concert hall was
a dim reflection of European _ and especially German _ art music,
with its sonatas and symphonies. After him, it was possible to feel
truly American. By RICHARD NILSEN. Story moved in the ``L'' and
``E'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NOTARO-COLUMN (Undated) - Heading toward L.A. in a 737, I wasn't
very happy, but I wasn't surprised. I've never had good luck with
airplanes. Once, while flying back from San Francisco, the pilot
nonchalantly announced as we approached Las Vegas that one of the
engines had simply dropped off the plane and was now hurling toward
the ground at a ferocious speed to become the headpiece for some
showgirl. By LAURI NOTARO. Story moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
