<HEADLINE>
$27.7M AGENCY DEAL UNITES ARNOLD, UK AD SHOP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By CHRIS REIDY  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The corporate parent of Arnold Communications has given it an
early holiday gift: its own English ad agency.
</P>
<P>
   Snyder Communications of Bethesda, Md., which bought Arnold in
March, said Wednesday it had acquired Partners BDDH of London in a
stock deal valued at $27.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   The deal will unite Boston-based Arnold, New England's largest
ad agency, with one of the largest independent ad agencies in the
United Kingdom. When expressed in terms of US dollars, Partners
BDDH projects annual billings are in the range of $120 million to
$140 million.
</P>
<P>
   With Volkswagen of America and regional groups of McDonald's
franchisees as some of its largest clients, Arnold projects annual
billings of $870 million.
</P>
<P>
   As a result, the deal could propel Arnold to its goal of being
the first New England ad agency to record $1 billion in annual
billings.
</P>
<P>
   Partners BDDH, which creates advertising in Europe for clients
such as Mercedes-Benz and Harley Davidson, will continue to operate
as a stand-alone unit, but its chief will report to Arnold chairman
Ed Eskandarian, said Snyder's chief financial officer Clay Perfall.
</P>
<P>
   ``Partners BDDH is now an Arnold Communications company,''
Eskandarian said. ``This will be our first step in international
expansion.''
</P>
<P>
   Partners BDDH is part of the Elan Network, an affiliation of
independent ad agencies in most major European countries.
</P>
<P>
   As a result, the acquisition will also give Arnold a toehold on
the Continent, Eskandarian said.
</P>
<P>
   For the moment, Partners BDDH will continue to operate under its
own name.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want to retain the characteristics of BDDH,'' said
Eskandarian, who added that those characteristics are very
``consistent'' with Arnold's, he said. Snyder specializes in
data-base direct marketing, and many key clients have been
pharmaceutical companies.
</P>
<P>
   In recent years, Snyder has been on an acquisition spree,
snapping up similar direct-marketing companies.
</P>
<P>
   Looking to broaden its expertise, Snyder began buying ad
agencies earlier this year. Arnold was its first purchase of a big
ad agency, and Partners BDDH is its second, Perfall said.
</P>
<P>
   After Snyder bought Arnold, Eskandarian was issued a mandate:
Buy more ad agencies. And Partners BDDH is his first big deal for
his new boss.
</P>
<P>
   ``With the additions of Arnold Communications and Partners BDDH,
Snyder Communications is positioned to offer our clients
world-class creative and brand-building services throughout the
United States, the United Kingdom, and Europe to match our
market-leading data-base and direct-marketing services,'' said
Snyder company founder Daniel M. Snyder in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   On the New York Stock Exchange, shares of Snyder fell 1 13/16 to
close at 33.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
