<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Foursome in driver's seats
 &HT;    By Richard L. Eldredge
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ After nearly 900 hours spent being cooped up in
Volkswagens, the Star 94 ``Live in It and Win It'' contestants
finally rode into the sunset Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after noon, with a crowd of spectators and TV crews
looking on, Kevin Danley, David Stephenson, John Crow and Sonja
Banks exited the red 1998 VW Beetle at North Point Mall in
Alpharetta(Ga.).
</P>
<P>
   The radio station had halted the contest with four participants
remaining, even though there were only two Beetles to award. So
each contestant was handed an envelope containing a slip of paper.
</P>
<P>
   Result: Banks snared the much-coveted black VW, and Crow won the
red model. Stephenson and Danley got one-year leases of black and
yellow Beetles _ which arrived for the occasion, honking their way
through the crowd.
</P>
<P>
   Former contestants Brenda Burke and Jennifer Roller also showed
up to congratulate the winners.
</P>
<P>
   The winning foursome plans to go to dinner and a movie next
week. There's even a one-year reunion on the schedule. Quipped
Banks: ``We're going to spend two days together in one of the cars
so we can catch up.''
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: buzz(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   For more juicy gossip and keen commentary, see what Vixana has
to say on ajc.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
