<HEADLINE>
USC'S WELCH MEDICALLY CLEARED TO PLAY AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC offensive lineman Matt Welch has been cleared
to play after tests revealed he experienced nothing more than a
rapid heart rate against Notre Dame last week.
</P>
<P>
   Welch was examined after being forced to leave Saturday's game
after experiencing a rapid heart rate. USC coach Paul Hackett said
it was a pre-existing condition. Tests done at USC University
Hospital detected no further problems, and Welch's heart rate
returned to normal during the tests.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
