<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, DECEMBER 3
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-EXXON-MOBIL-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Dec. 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Dec. 1,
about the merger agreement between the Exxon Corporation and Mobil
Corporation misattributed a statement disclosing the first
discussions held by the companies with the Federal Trade
Commission. The disclosure was made at a news conference by Lee R.
Raymond, the chairman and chief executive of Exxon, not by Federal
Trade Commission officials.
</P>
<P>
   BC-IMPEACH-NYT (moved on Monday, Nov. 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Nov. 30,
about the House Judiciary Committee hearings on impeachment
misstated the context for a statement by Joe Lockhart, the White
House press secretary. When Mr. Lockhart said, ``It won't add any
new information and can be put in the category of a stunt,'' he was
speaking about the committee's plans to hold a hearing on the
consequences of perjury, not about its invitation to President
Clinton to testify.
</P>
<P>
   BC-TRITIUM-SHORTAGE-NYT (moved on Saturday, Nov. 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, Nov. 28,
about American production of tritium misspelled the surname of a
senior fellow at the Council on Foreign Relations who suggested
buying the material from Russia. He is Richard Garwin, not Garland.
</P>
</TEXT>
