<HEADLINE>
THURSDAY NFL MATCHUP: EAGLES VS. RAMS 
</HEADLINE>
  (bl) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Rams coach Dick Vermeil left Philadelphia in 1982 because he was
burned out. Eagles coach Ray Rhodes will likely be leaving soon
because he didn't win many games. Two emotional coaches with bad
teams take center stage in this battle-for-pride drama. Vermeil
said Tony Banks, not Steve Bono, will again start at quarterback.
How bad is the Eagles' offense? Last week, Koy Detmer threw
Philadelphia's first two touchdown passes of the season to wide
receivers. They may not score Thursday night, but Rhodes wins a
game that only gamblers and players' families may watch.
</P>
<P>
   EAGLES 9, RAMS 7
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
