<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-TCU-BOWL-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEXAS CHRISTIAN IN BOWL PICTURE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Think TCU playing in a bowl game on New
Year's Eve sounds crazy? Well, don't. It could happen.
</P>
<P>
   TCU officials plan to travel to El Paso today to meet with
officials from the Sun Bowl to talk about the possibility of the
Horned Frogs filling an at-large slot to play Southern Cal.
</P>
<P>
   Bowl bids will officially be extended Sunday, and TCU, a team
that went 1-10 in 1997 and finished fifth in the Mountain Division
this season, could be among the recipients.
</P>
<P>
   ``They are one of the teams we are considering,'' said John
Folmer, the chairman of the Sun Bowl selection committee. ``It's a
long shot. A lot of things need to happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Actually, one really big domino needs to fall.
</P>
<P>
   For TCU (6-5) to be considered, Ohio State needs to be selected
as one of the two at-large teams for one of the four Bowl
Championship Series games.
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State (10-1) is ranked fifth in the BCS rankings.
</P>
<P>
   If no upsets happen in Saturday's games, the BCS's four bowls
could look like this: Fiesta _ Tennessee vs. UCLA; Rose _ Arizona
vs. Wisconsin; Sugar _ Kansas State vs. Ohio State; and Orange _
Syracuse vs. Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   If Ohio State goes to one of the four BCS bowls, the Big Ten
would have four remaining bowl-eligible teams. To be bowl eligible,
teams need to have six victories against Division I-A teams.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Bowl has contracts with the Big Ten and Pacific-10, and
is supposed to feature the No. 4 team in the PAC-10 against the No.
5 team in the Big Ten, Purdue.
</P>
<P>
   But if Ohio State goes to a BCS bowl, that opens another bowl
slot for a Big Ten team. Purdue would go to the Alamo Bowl, and the
Sun Bowl would get the team with the next best record in the Big
Ten.
</P>
<P>
   Michigan State (6-6) is the Big Ten's next team in line, but
NCAA rules say if a team plays 12 games, it has to win seven of
those to be bowl eligible.
</P>
<P>
   ``We understand that certain things have to happen, but just to
be sitting here on Dec. 2 in this position is pretty neat,'' Horned
Frogs coach Dennis Franchione said. ``We'll just hope for a little
luck.''
</P>
<P>
   If the Big Ten is unable to fulfill its contract to the Sun
Bowl, Folmer said the bowl would then look at the remaining
eligible teams to fill the slot.
</P>
<P>
   ``The list is rather short,'' Folmer said.
</P>
<P>
   Folmer said some of the teams that are being considered are
Central Florida (9-2), Miami, Ohio (10-1) and three Western
Athletic Conference teams _ Colorado State (8-4), Utah (7-4) and
Wyoming (8-4).
</P>
<P>
   Colorado State and Wyoming both defeated TCU this season. They
are also schools that announced plans this spring to leave the WAC
to form the Mountain West.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Bowl is on the campus of Texas-El Paso, one of the eight
remaining WAC schools.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've already gotten calls from fans in Wyoming saying: `Why
won't they take us. We beat TCU?' '' Folmer said. ``There are more
people in the city of Fort Worth than the state of Wyoming. . . .
Besides, TCU has had an exciting season. They won one game last
year, and this season's turnaround under Dennis Franchione is
exciting.''
</P>
<P>
   TCU last went to a bowl in 1994, a 20-10 loss to Virginia in the
Independence Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   After 1997's 1-10 season, former coach Pat Sullivan resigned,
Franchione was brought in and the Frogs went 6-5.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yes, I've exceeded my wildest expectations by far,''
Franchione said. ``It brings a big smile to your face. It's great
for the university, great for the kids just to be in this
position.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
